# Patch target: @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.76 cli.js
# Original SHA-256: 38b8fd29d0817e5f75202b2bb211fe959d4b6a4f2224b8118dabf876e503b50b
# Patched SHA-256:  6ea2a57ddd49c3f0869e77e027f3de0c2116c390a0d338963f70bec9b92b537c
#
# What this does:
#   Adds `return;` at the start of _Oz() (bridge URL resolver).
#   This makes _Oz() always return undefined, so bridgeConfig is never set,
#   forcing Xd1() to use the local socket pool (pzA) instead of BridgeClient (y61).
#
# Why:
#   The tengu_copper_bridge server-side feature flag enables the WebSocket bridge
#   for Max subscribers. The bridge fails to connect on Windows, and there is no
#   fallback to local named pipes. The local pipe (\\.\pipe\claude-mcp-browser-bridge-{user})
#   works perfectly.
